comments.message:
So... Richard told me he was using "mod_" for internal imports and got a CR telling him that "mod_" should only be for external imports. Guessing that was jclulow. Jclulow-originating repos have "var lib_foo = require('./foo')" examples.

node-urclient/lib/ur_client.js:var lib_inflight = require('./inflight');
sdc-hagfish-watcher/lib/service.js:var lib_common = require('./common');
sdc-hermes/lib/servers.js:var lib_utils = require('./utils');

and Richard started following suite in triton-cmon[-agent].git. I don't think either is really codified in eng docs, tho "mod_foo" is certainly a pattern in roughly half of them. :)
